17    /**
18    * A method delegation binder is responsible for creating a method binding for a <i>source method</i> to a
19    * <i>target method</i>. Such a binding allows to implement the source method by calling the target method.
20    * <p>&nbsp;</p>
21    * Usually, an implementation will attempt to bind a specific source method to a set of target method candidates
22    * where all legal bindings are considered for binding. To chose a specific candidate, an
23    * {@link net.bytebuddy.implementation.bind.MethodDelegationBinder.AmbiguityResolver}
24    * will be consulted for selecting a <i>best</i> binding.
25    */
 
- Uncovered Elements: 0 (0) Complexity: 0 Complexity Density: -
26    public interface MethodDelegationBinder {
27   
28    /**
29    * Attempts a binding of a source method to a given target method.
30    *
31    * @param implementationTarget The target of the current implementation onto which this binding
32    * is to be applied.
33    * @param source The method that is to be bound to the {@code target} method.
34    * @param target The method that is to be invoked as a delegate.
35    * @return A binding representing this attempt to bind the {@code source} method to the {@code target} method.
36    */
37    MethodBinding bind(Implementation.Target implementationTarget,
38    MethodDescription source,
39    MethodDescription target);
